One year 💕 Love you to the moon and back 

AND officially one year and 3 months off Instagram !! Loved it but missed it - more life updates coming soon 💕
what a fun weekend of celebrating in SD !! @rachelcataylor bday, one year with @newmannewworld, and TWO MFA acceptances 🥰
Film is my favorite - here are some photos from my travels over the last year :)
Amsterdam on film 📸
Film from Niagara Falls 🌈💦 Went on a research trip for my novel this past fall :)
Paris on film - spent a month there this past summer taking a writing class at American University of Paris :) Going back in June to spend 6 weeks studying French - can’t wait!

My day today 💕 got an impromptu tattoo bc I’m MOVING BACK TO NORTH CAROLINA !!! 15 months ago, I quit Instagram to prioritize my writing and I have been writing every. single. day. since then. I applied to SEVENTEEN MFA programs this December, got into four (waitlisted at 2), and just decided today to accept my offer as University of North Carolina Wilmington. I cannot wait to write, and teach, and live at the beach for the next three years. I am so happy and so proud of myself and still feel like it’s not real that the thing I love is going to be my main thing - not what I do before or after work or on weekends. Everybody better come visit me!!

Some solo shots of 🌟ME🌟 from the last year to prove that even though I was off insta, I was not any less annoying 
-Miami for @sofia_lenore wedding 
-Anguilla for my birthday 
-On the way to the hot tub after skiing 
-Me, THRILLED, after a trip to Claire’s 
-At a monster truck rally LOL

-Punting in Oxford (I was horrible!) 
-Graduating from Oxfords summer writing program 
-Halloween - let them eat 🎂🍰🧁
The most lovely day with my favorite people 💕💕
This weekend! ☀️ also I feel like I really need these glasses? (Picture 8 lmk)
28 🎂 I’m as excited about this cake my mom got me as I am about this next year 💕 So thankful for everyone that made yesterday so special 🖤
Love my friends !! Had the best time celebrating @newmannewworld and I’s birthdays yesterday! Now off to spring break 💕
“Can’t wait to get on the board” - @newmannewworld , referring to playing chess, not surfing ☀️ Great first day at the beach 💕 Started reading Bunny and cannot recommend it enough !
Can’t wait to be a seahawk! So fun this week to see my future apartment, my future school, my future town 🤗

I sent my novel to agents today !!! The Icarus Project started as a short story at an Oxford workshop this past summer, and over the course of the last year has grown into a whole novel! I am so proud of this book and everything I did to make it a reality — took a research trip to Niagara Falls, went on a writing retreat @getawayhouse to finish my first draft, got feedback from 20+ beta readers, and invented a new writing pose called The Writing Gargoyle ™️ Now I’ve just got to keep my fingers crossed that the querying process works out 🤞🏻Thank you so much to everyone who has helped me along the way!! 🖤
The best first day … now onto the DERBY !! 👒💸🐎🐴🧲🌸🌷
Lost some money, made some memories 👒🤗🐴 first Kentucky derby in the books!
CONGRATS @ellie_beuley !! Thanks for such a fun graduation weekend - I’m so proud of you!! Wahoowa!!

And that’s a wrap on an incredible last week at Haynes! Today was my last day of teaching after four years!! In these four years, I have met some of the most amazing kids and worked with some of the most amazing people! I’m going to MISS YALL!! 💕💕 love you guys 😊😊 While these last four years certainly haven’t been easy, they have had an immense impact on me - shown me that I love teaching, introduced me to some incredible people (my boyfriend included), and taught me many more lessons besides. I am so thankful for this experience, and I am so glad that this won’t be the end of my teaching career - can’t wait to teach creative writing next year!

A great last week !!! NOW OFF TO PARIS !! I’m gonna miss DC and all my amazing friends here. Four years ago, I moved to DC for a teaching program - I thought I’d get my degree and head back to NYC, but I really found my place here 💕 so DC, this isn’t goodbye, but see you later!! I’ll be back in 3 years with an MFA!! 😭🤗💕🎉

Welcome to my beach house! I officially live at Wrightsville Beach now! So excited for this next chapter :) If you’re ever here, let me know - I want visitors!
One full week in Wrightsville ☀️ Feeling so lucky

Leaving Wrightsville for the next 10 days to attend the Breadloaf Writers Conference !! I still can’t believe I got in! Get excited for some Vermont pictures 🤗 Then the day I get back is my first day of classes at UNCW - so much writing!
Pinch me! I am in the most beautiful place, surrounded by writers, writing, reading, and learning all day 🍞📚📝

Breadloaf 2023 is coming to a close 🥺 While I’m so sad to leave the amazing people I’ve met here and this beautiful place, I’m leaving with so many book recommendations and so many kind, supportive, talented writer friends :) I can’t believe it’s only been ten days - it feels like a lifetime! So grateful for this experience 💕 love y’all!
“You can make anything by writing” - C.S. Lewis 🍞 Breadloaf 2023
My first visitors!! Everyone come see me! ☀️🌊🤗
Second full week in Wrightsville in the books! Spent most the week writing in my little beach cottage and reading on the beach :)
Week 3 in Wrightsville: Riverwalk, Museum of the Bizarre, new writer friends, porch nights, pasta, beach reads, birthdays, and volleyball 🌊
Week 4 in Wrightsville: Girls nights, First Year Reading, rainy days, cozy sweaters, morning walks, fairy tales, and a new nanny job ✍🏻☀️🌊🤗
Week 5 in Wrightsville: Disposable cameras, Rachel and Henry visiting, our dogs meeting, and more beach days ☀️
Week 6 in Wrightsville: Fall decorations, weekend trip to DC, and sunrise walks
Week 7 in Wrightsville 💕 This place has my heart :)
Week 8: Second Trip to DC and film developed from first trip :)
Week 9: parents in town, @_carolinelewis in town, and Halloweekend with my besties :)
Video roundup from November :) It’s been a great month 💕
Happy moments from November 🎄
Memories from the best 60th birthday celebration for @bethbeuley in Charlottesville! Swipe to see my dads incredible wrapping job! Somewhere there is a group photo, but alas I cannot find it
December at the beach :)

Four months ago, I went to a writing conference. It was ten days long, and I was so nervous the first day - nervous about my writing - and nervous that I wouldn’t connect with anyone. I still have to pinch myself when I think this is how it turned out - with writer friends who will travel across the country to see each other 🤗 Had the best weekend in LA with @aimee_clemens and @katie_daltonn 💕
Rang in the New Year in Shenandoah. So excited for 2024 :)
